Today, Nigeria and the rest of the world is celebrating the World Town Planning Day (WTPD), an international day for celebrating the accomplishments of town planners and their contributions to communities,  the Nigerian Institute of Town Planners (NITP) has said. Nathaniel Atebije, National Vice President of NITP, in a statement, said:  “The main issues of consideration for this year center on equality and diversity, environment and climate change, sustainable and healthy communities and economic development. This is intended to provoke actions and promote urban planning as an important tool for achieving the components of the sustainable development goals and addressing the challenges of climate change, inequalities and respect for humanity across the world with particular reference to our national environment’’, he said. He said the celebration of this day in 2019 is spectacular because it is the 70th anniversary. Town planners task govts on planning, urban renewal National conference minus Nigerian town planners ... Want strict adherence to master plan Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.